4 ounce Grape Tomatoes
8 ounce Broccoli
4 ounce Bacon
1 teaspoon Garlic Powder
10 ounce Seasoned Precooked Potato Slices
½ cup Cheddar Cheese
1.5 ounce Buttermilk Ranch Dressing
1.5 tablespoon Sour Cream
Salt
Pepper
1 teaspoon Hot Sauce

• Wash and dry produce.
• Cut bacon* crosswise into 1⁄2-inch pieces.
• Heat a large dry, preferably nonstick, pan over
medium-high heat. Add bacon and cook,
stirring occasionally, until bacon begins to
crisp and fat renders, 4 minutes. (The bacon
will finish cooking in the next step.)
• Meanwhile, in a medium microwave-safe
bowl, combine broccoli, garlic powder,
1 TBSP water (2 TBSP for 4 servings), a pinch
of salt, and pepper. Cover with plastic wrap
and microwave until tender, 1-2 minutes. Set
aside for use in the next step.

• Add potatoes and tomatoes to pan with
bacon; season with a pinch of salt and pepper.
(If there’s not enough bacon fat, add a drizzle
of oil.) Cook, undisturbed, until potatoes
are crispy on one side and bacon is cooked
through, 3-5 minutes. Stir, gently scraping up
any crispy bits on the bottom. TIP: If potatoes
start to stick to the pan, add a splash of water.
• Top potato skillet with broccoli. Sprinkle
everything with cheddar. Cover and cook until
cheese melts, 1-2 minutes.

• Divide potato, broccoli, and bacon skillet
between plates. Serve with sour cream, ranch
dressing, and hot sauce on the side.

***Pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.***